For your background in backend systems and AI engineering, the most practical path is **not** to train an SLM entirely from scratch.
Instead, start with an open-weight base model (such as Qwen, Llama, or Mistral), perform **continued pretraining** on your domain data if
needed, apply **instruction fine-tuning** (LoRA/QLoRA), optionally combine it with **RAG**, and then deploy it with a high-performance inference server. 
This approach delivers most of the benefits of a domain-specific SLM while requiring a fraction of the compute and data needed for full pretraining.

