The **planner service** decides *which retrievals, tools, or actions are needed*. The **reasoning service** interprets the gathered information and produces the final conclusion. 
Both services can use the **same underlying SLM or LLM**, but with different prompts and orchestration logic. This separation makes the system easier to test, maintain, and extend.

Q: Build VLM from scratch?

A **Vision Language Model (VLM)** extends a language model so it can understand images in addition to text. Unlike an LLM, which only processes tokens, a VLM combines a **vision encoder** with a **language model** through a connector (projection) layer.

For your enterprise AI goals, you would almost always **build on an existing open-weight VLM** rather than train one from scratch. But if you want to understand the complete pipeline, here's the end-to-end architecture.

---

# What is a VLM?

```text
Image + Text
      │
      ▼
Vision Encoder
      │
      ▼
Projection Layer
      │
      ▼
Language Model
      │
      ▼
Generated Response
```

The vision encoder converts pixels into embeddings that the language model can understand.

